IndexPage.description: Demo of Next.js 16 cacheComponents with next-intl. Shows the difference between dynamic and cached components using getTranslations() with the 'use cache' directive.
IndexPage.title: cacheComponents Demo with next-intl

dynamicComponent.title: Dynamic Component
dynamicComponent.content: Uses getTranslations() without explicit locale parameter, relying on request context. Cannot be cached due to context dependency.

cachedComponent.title: Cached Component
cachedComponent.content: Uses 'use cache' directive and receives locale as prop, then calls getTranslations({locale}). Explicit locale parameter makes it cacheable.

PathnamesPage.description:
The pathnames are internationalized too.

If you're using the default language English, you'll see /en/pathnames in the browser address bar on this page.

If you change the locale to German, the URL is localized accordingly (/de/pfadnamen).
PathnamesPage.title: Pathnames
